20hydrogen%20hubs%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrawing%20from%20natural%20reservoirs%20of%20hydrogen%20would%20be%20much%20cleaner%20%E2%80%94%20if%20it's%20worth%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-approval-alaska-drilling-could-be-big-oils-last-surge-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrilling%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20hydrogen%20gold%20rush%20is%20beginning%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20relatively%20new%20prospect.%20In%20fact%2C%20scientists%20didn't%20believe%20it%20was%20possible%20for%20large%20amounts%20of%20hydrogen%20to%20accumulate%20underground%20until%20about%2012%20years%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20Ellis%2C%20who%20leads%20USGS%20efforts%20to%20map%20the%20world's%20potential%20reserves%20of%20underground%20hydrogen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffossil-fuel-companies-spend-millions-to-promote-individual-responsibility-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoil%20and%20gas%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20assessed%20a%20mine%20that%20had%20exploded%20in%20Mali%20and%20found%20it%20was%20full%20of%20hydrogen%20gas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHydrogen%20forms%20deep%20underground%20when%20water%20reacts%20with%20iron-rich%20rock.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20two%20long%20stretches%20of%20this%20rock%20are%20a%20promising%20place%20to%20look%20for%20hydrogen%20reserves%2C%20and%20efforts%20are%20already%20underway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20stretch%20runs%20from%20Kansas%20up%20to%20Ontario%2C%20then%20down%20to%20Michigan.%20The%20other%20is%20offshore%2C%20running%20the%20length%20of%20New%20Jersey%20to%20Georgia%2C%20according%20to%20Ellis.%20USGS%20started%20looking%20for%20these%20reserves%20in%202021%20and%20has%20drilled%20several%20wells%2C%20with%20more%20planned%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEllis%20told%20the%20Senate%20committee%20that%20research%20is%20also%20ongoing%20in%20France%20and%20Australia%2C%20and%20active%20exploration%20efforts%20are%20underway%20in%20Brazil%20and%20Colombia.%20In%20February%2C%20researchers%20announced%20they%20had%20discovered%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fresearchers-discover-albanian-mine-could-be-hydrogen-source-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehydrogen%20reservoir%20in%20a%20mine%20in%20Albania%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22594%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bulqiz%C3%AB%20chromite%20mine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e4c438ce7f1785b2e5c0a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22396%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Bulqiz%C3%AB%20chromite%20mine%20just%2025%20miles%20east%20of%20Albania's%20capital%20Tirana%20contains%20a%20huge%20reservoir%20of%20hydrogen.%3Cp%3EGENT%20SHKULLAKU%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompanies%20exploring%20for%20geologic%20hydrogen%20use%20many%20of%20the%20same%20technologies%20that%20are%20used%20in%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20Senator%20John%20Barrasso%20(R-WY)%20said%20in%20the%20hearing.%20%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20many%20of%20the%20people%20exploring%20for%20hydrogen%20today%20spent%20their%20careers%20exploring%20for%20oil%20and%20gas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20still%20unclear%20how%20much%20hydrogen%20is%20out%20there%2C%20or%20how%20much%20it%20will%20cost%20to%20extract%20it.%20So%20the%20DOE's%20Advanced%20Research%20Projects%20Agency-Energy%20is%20doling%20out%20%2420%20million%20in%20grants%20to%20fund%20research%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20including%20the%20possibility%20of%20artificially%20stimulating%20the%20natural%20process%20that%20makes%20hydrogen%20underground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20our%20programs%20show%20success%2C%20this%20new%20source%20of%20hydrogen%20could%20lower%20energy%20costs%20and%20increase%20our%20nation's%20energy%20security%20and%20supply%20chains%2C%26quot%3B%20Evelyn%20N.%20Wang%2C%20director%20of%20ARPA-E%2C%20told%20the%20Senate%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20the%20fuel%20would%20face%20some%20of%20the%20same%20challenges%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-hydrogen-fuel-industry-explainer-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanufactured%20hydrogen%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20may%20not%20be%20enough%20infrastructure%20to%20transport%20it%20far%20and%20wide.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20any%20hydrogen%20that%20leaks%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20would%20react%20with%20other%20compounds%20to%20cause%20the%20atmosphere%20to%20trap%20more%20heat.%20That%20could%20cancel%20out%20hydrogen's%20climate%20advantage%20over%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20has%20all%20the%20answers%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Koloma%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20Pete%20Johnson%20told%20the%20Senate%20committee.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20early%20data%20looks%20very%20promising%20and%20I%20believe%20that%20geologic%20hydrogen%20can%20play%20a%20very%20large%20role%20as%20we%20work%20to%20decarbonize%20the%20US%20energy%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclean-hydrogen-fuel-reserves-could-be-hiding-underground-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709848538000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e9f212ce7f1785b2e76809%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclean-hydrogen-fuel-reserves-could-be-hiding-underground-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Clean%20hydrogen%20gas%20from%20underground%20reservoirs%20could%20be%20a%20key%20source%20of%20carbon-free%20fuel.%20Bill%20Gates%20and%20Amazon%20are%20investing%20in%20early%20exploration.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmcfalljohnsen%40businessinsider.com%20(Morgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A59%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclean-hydrogen-fuel-reserves-could-be-hidin