0candidate%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20greets%20supporters%20at%20Mar-a-Lago%20in%20Palm%20Beach%2C%20Florida.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FRebecca%20Blackwel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDonald%20Trump%20is%20suing%20the%20Pulitzer%20Prize%20Board%20for%20awarding%20coverage%20of%20his%20ties%20to%20Russia.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20board%20said%20two%20independent%20reviews%20concluded%20the%20prizes%20should%20stand.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20depositions%2C%20his%20lawyers%20are%20seen%20hunting%20for%20the%20identities%20of%20those%20anonymous%20reviewers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20overlooked%20lawsuit%2C%20Donald%20Trump's%20lawyers%20are%20exhibiting%20a%20habit%20from%20his%20White%20House%20days%3A%20Hunting%20for%20anonymous%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20transcripts%20of%20four%20depositions%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Trump's%20attorneys%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20question%20journalists%20about%20a%20mystery%20that%20has%20vexed%20them%20for%20years%3A%20Who%20are%20the%20anonymous%20consultants%20who%20reviewed%20the%20Pulitzer%20Prizes%20awarded%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20and%20The%20Washington%20Post%20for%20their%20coverage%20of%20Trump's%20connections%20to%20Russia%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20depositions%20were%20taken%20last%20year%20for%20a%20lawsuit%20Trump%20brought%20in%20December%202022%2C%20suing%20the%20Pulitzer%20Prize%20Board%2C%20which%20administers%20American%20journalism's%20highest%20honors.%20He%20accused%20the%20board%20and%20its%2018%20members%20of%20defaming%20him%20by%20awarding%20the%202018%20Pulitzer%20Prize%20for%20National%20Reporting%20to%20The%20Washington%20Post%20and%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20for%20their%20coverage%20of%20Russia's%20interference%20in%20the%202016%20election%20and%20the%20country's%20connections%20to%20Trump's%20presidential%20campaign%20and%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20lawsuit%2C%20Trump%20complained%20that%20journalists%20and%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20conspired%20together%20as%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20%26quot%3BRussia%20Collusion%20Hoax%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20the%20former%20president%20claimed%20was%20%26quot%3Bfully%20debunked.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20reality%2C%20investigations%20from%20Robert%20Mueller%20and%20a%20US%20Senate%20intelligence%20committee%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-campaign-russia-government-contact-timeline-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enumerous%20connections%20between%20Russian%20efforts%20and%20the%20Trump%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20even%20as%20they%20did%20not%20conclude%20that%20Trump%20personally%20fostered%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20Trump's%20lawsuit%20focuses%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpulitzer-board-rejects-trump-rescind-awards-new-york-times-post-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20July%202022%20statement%20from%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20it%20announced%20the%20prizes%20would%20stand%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-demanding-nyt-and-wapo-journalists-get-their-pulitzers-rescinded-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%20called%20on%20it%20to%20rescind%20the%20awards%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pulitzer.org%2Fnews%2Fstatement-pulitzer-prize-board-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20board%20announced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20commissioned%20%26quot%3Btwo%20independent%20reviews%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20work%20submitted%20by%20the%20Times%20and%20the%20Post%20that%20won%20the%202018%20prize%2C%20which%20%26quot%3Bwere%20conducted%20by%20individuals%20with%20no%20connection%20to%20the%20institutions%20whose%20work%20was%20under%20examination%2C%20nor%20any%20connection%20to%20each%20other.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20review%20independently%20concluded%20the%20prize-winning%20stories%20were%20not%20%26quot%3Bdiscredited%20by%20facts%20that%20emerged%20subsequent%20to%20the%20conferral%20of%20the%20prizes%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20board%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20this%20day%2C%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20has%20not%20disclosed%20who%20did%20the%20reviews%20and%20what%20they%20consisted%20of.%20Nor%20have%20its%20members%20explained%20why%20they%20are%20keeping%20the%20information%20a%20secret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20lawyers%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20it.%20In%20the%20depositions%20Business%20Insider%20obtained%2C%20Trump's%20lawyers%20question%20the%20defendants%20%E2%80%94%20all%20journalists%20%E2%80%94%20about%20what%20they%20describe%20as%20their%20%26quot%3Buse%20of%20anonymous%20sources%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20Pulitzer%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithout%20identifying%20those%20individuals%2C%20I%20guess%20we%20have%20no%20way%20to%20verify%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20statement%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump's%20lawyer%20R.%20Quincy%20Bird%20asked%20investigative%20journalist%20Katherine%20Boo%20in%20her%20deposition%2C%20taken%20in%20August%202023.%20%26quot%3BSo%20Ms.%20Boo%2C%20I'll%20ask%20it%20directly%2C%20who%20conducted%20the%20external%20review%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20each%20turn%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20the%20Pulitzer%20Board%20members%20stopped%20their%20clients%20from%20answering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hunt%20for%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20Pulitzer%20board's%20reviewers%20demonstrates%20how%20some%20of%20Trump's%20attitudes%20toward%20media%20%E2%80%94%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-white-house-bunker-leaker-treason-executed-book-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobsession%20with%20anonymous%20sources%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20paranoia%20of%20supposed%20shadowy%20figures%20he%20claims%20to%20believe%20are%20conspiring%20against%20him%20%E2%80%94%20have%20leaked%20beyond%20the%20political%20arena%20and%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-key-cases-civil-criminal-investigations-lawsuits-updates-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20lawsuits%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChad%20R.%20Bowman%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20the%20law%20firm%20Ballard%20Spahr%2C%20said%20in%20a%20deposition%20transcript%20that%20the%20identities%20of%20the%20people%20who%20conducted%20the%20reviews%20for%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20were%20subject%20to%20%26quot%3BFirst%20Amendment%20privilege%20to%20protect%20sources.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20instruct%20the%20witness%20not%20to%20answer%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20First%20Amendment%20privilege%2C%26quot%3B%20Bowman%20said%20in%20the%20deposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20lawyers%20indicated%20they%20disagreed%20with%20Bowman's%20assertion%2C%20but%20haven't%20yet%20filed%20any%20court%20motions%20asking%20the%20judge%20to%20force%20the%20defendants%20to%20identify%20the%20reviewers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20step%20normally%20taken%20when%20lawyers%20don't%20get%20the%20answers%20they%20want%20during%20a%20deposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarjorie%20Miller%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pulitzer.org%2Fnews%2Fjournalist-marjorie-miller-elected-administrator-pulitzer-prizes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20administrator%20of%20the%20Pulitzer%20Prizes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20at%20liberty%20to%20discuss%20this%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20journalists%20whom%20Trump's%20lawyers%20deposed%20did%2C%20however%2C%20offer%20some%20characterization%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bconsultants%26quot%3B%20who%20conducted%20the%20reviews.%20Miller%2C%20who%20sat%20for%20a%20deposition%20on%20May%2023%20last%20year%2C%20testified%20the%20people%20were%20%26quot%3Bwidely%20recognized%20as%20leaders%26quot%3B%20in%20American%20journalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoo%20told%20Trump's%20lawyers%20that%20she%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20first%20review%2C%20which%20took%20place%20in%202019.%20She%20said%20she%20had%20confidence%20in%20the%20results%20of%20the%20second%20review%2C%20which%20took%20place%20in%202021%2C%20and%20took%20additional%20information%20into%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20person%20who%20had%20no%20relationship%20and%20person%20who%20had%20the%20stature%20and%2C%20I%20believe%2C%20ethical%20clarity%20and%20the%20moral%20rigor%20to%20be%20frank%20with%20the%20board%20should%20problems%20with%20those%20submissions%20be%20submitted%2C%26quot%3B%20Boo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20depositions%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20Pulitzer's%20secretive%20reviews%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20attacks%20on%20journalism%20remain%20a%20pillar%20of%20his%20political%20message.%20And%20he%20has%20extended%20his%20language%20railing%20against%20a%20%26quot%3Bwitch%20hunt%26quot%3B%20against%20him%20to%20include%20his%20many%20legal%20problems%20%E2%80%94%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-criminal-cases-ranked-how-much-legal-trouble-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20separate%20grand%20jury%20criminal%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20as%20he%20runs%20in%20the%202024%20presidential%20election.%20In%202023%2C%20a%20PAC%20Trump%20controls%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-legal-fees-pac-donor-money-personal-cases-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egave%20over%20%24260%2C000%20in%20donor%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Weber%2C%20Crabb%2C%20%26amp%3B%20Wein%2C%20the%20law%20firm%20representing%20him%20in%20the%20Pulitzer%20case%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Insider%20analysis%20of%20disbursement%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pulitzer%20Prize%20Board%20is%20hosted%20by%20Columbia%20University%2C%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20which%20manages%20the%20small%20organization's%20payroll%20and%20offers%20institutional%20support.%20But%20Trump%20brought%20his%20lawsuit%20in%20Florida%2C%20arguing%20the%20state%20has%20jurisdiction%20in%20the%20defamation%20lawsuit%20because%20he%20lives%20at%20Mar-a-Lago.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20lawsuit%20also%20points%20out%20that%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20includes%20Neil%20Brown%2C%20a%20Florida%20resident%20who%20serves%20as%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Poynter%20Institute%20for%20Media%20Studies%20and%20worked%20as%20the%20top%20editor%20at%20the%20Tampa%20Bay%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20judge%20overseeing%20the%20case%20blocked%20Trump's%20lawyers%20from%20issuing%20subpoenas%20for%20depositions%20and%20records%20for%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20case%2C%20allowing%20only%20jurisdictional%20discovery.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20defendants%20%E2%80%94%20which%20include%20New%20Yorker%20editor%20in%20chief%20David%20Remnick%2C%20USA%20Today%20editor%20in%20chief%20Nicole%20Carroll%2C%20former%20Columbia%20University%20president%20Lee%20Bollinger%2C%20former%20Los%20Angeles%20Times%20executive%20editor%20Kevin%20Merida%2C%20and%20novelist%20Viet%20Thanh%20Nguyen%2C%20among%20others%20%E2%80%94%20all%20submitted%20paperwork%20describing%20their%20lack%20of%20connections%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228803%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22marjorie%20miller%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ea20726080194819fdbff1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226602%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAssociated%20Press%20Vice%20President%20and%20Global%20Enterprise%20Editor%20Marjorie%20Miller%20stands%20for%20a%20portrait%20in%20the%20news%20agency's%20New%20York%20City%20headquarters%2C%20Tuesday%2C%20Mar.%2C%2029%2C%202022.%20On%20Thursday%2C%20March%2031%2C%202022%2C%20the%20Pulitzer%20Prize%20Board%20and%20Lee%20C.%20Bollinger%2C%20president%20of%20Columbia%20University%2C%20which%20hosts%20the%20prestigious%20journalism%20awards%2C%20announced%20Miller%20has%20been%20named%20as%20the%20new%20administrator%20of%20the%20Pulitzer%20Prizes.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FJ.%20David%20Ake%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20lawyers%20deposed%20Miller%2C%20along%20with%20three%20board%20members%20who%20served%20as%20cochairs%20when%20the%202022%20statement%20was%20issued%3A%20Katherine%20Boo%2C%20New%20York%20Times%20opinion%20columnist%20Gail%20Collins%2C%20and%20Associated%20Press%20standards%20editor%20John%20Daniszewski.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20depositions%20were%20supposed%20to%20focus%20on%20obtaining%20information%20to%20bolster%20Trump's%20jurisdictional%20arguments.%20But%20his%20lawyer's%20questions%20frequently%20went%20outside%20those%20lines%2C%20Bowman%20complained%20during%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20Miller's%20deposition%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20Bird%20attempted%20to%20ask%20questions%20about%20how%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20came%20to%20hire%20her%20in%20the%20administrator%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCounsel%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20engage%20in%20argument%20with%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Bowman%20snapped.%20%26quot%3BI%20disagree%20that%20you%20can%20ask%20any%20question%20whether%20or%20not%20it's%20relating%20to%20jurisdiction%20because%20it%20has%20some%20tie%20to%20a%20document.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20members%20declined%20to%20identify%20who%20conducted%20the%20reviews%2C%20their%20depositions%20shed%20some%20light%20on%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniszewski%20said%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20had%20%26quot%3Bengaged%20two%20outside%20consultants%26quot%3B%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tenure%20of%20the%20administrator%20who%20preceded%20Miller%2C%20the%20publisher%20Dana%20Canady%2C%20to%20consider%20%26quot%3Bfive%20or%20six%20complaints%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20prizes.%20Some%20of%20those%20complaints%20were%20about%20historical%20issues%2C%20and%20one%20was%20about%20Trump's%20complaint%20about%20the%20prizes%20to%20the%20Times%20and%20the%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20recommended%20to%20the%20board%20that%20no%20action%20be%20taken%20and%20that%20the%20basis%20for%20the%20complaint%20was%20unfounded%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniszewski%20said%20in%20his%20deposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20complaints%20from%20Trump%20rolled%20in%2C%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20debated%20whether%20to%20conduct%20another%20review.%20Boo%2C%20Miller%2C%20and%20Daniszewski%20all%20said%20the%20board%20gets%20occasional%20complaints%20and%20doesn't%20always%20find%20them%20worth%20addressing%2C%20but%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20took%20Trump's%20criticism%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20everyone%20on%20the%20board%20agreed%20that%20the%20facts%20in%20the%20case%20warranted%20external%20review%2C%20and%20there%20was%20a%20debate%2C%20and%20the%20majority%20decided%20that%20it%20did%20warrant%20external%20review%2C%26quot%3B%20Boo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225570%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%222018%20pulitzer%20prize%20winners%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ea214b6080194819fdc0cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223258%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E2018%20Pulitzer%20Prize%20winners%20pose%20for%20pictures%20during%20the%20awards%20luncheon%20and%20ceremony%20at%20Columbia%20University%20in%20New%20York.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FBebeto%20Matthews%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Trump%20and%20his%20lawyers%20had%20explicitly%20demanded%20that%20the%20Pulitzers%20rescind%20the%20prize%20%E2%80%94%20and%20made%20a%20series%20of%20specific%20complaints%20in%20a%20series%20of%20letters%20%E2%80%94%20the%20board%20decided%20to%20commission%20a%20reexamination%20of%20the%20articles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20we%20believed%20that%20we%20had%20already%20looked%20at%20it%2C%20we%20thought%20we%20should%20do%20our%20diligence%20and%20reexamine%20the%20question%20because%20it%20was%20coming%20from%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniszewski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20members%20said%20that%20the%20people%20who%20conducted%20the%20two%20independent%20reviews%20of%20the%20Times'%20and%20Posts'%20Pulitzer%20submissions%20did%20not%20live%20in%20Florida%2C%20nor%20did%20they%20have%20an%20affiliation%20with%20the%20Times%20or%20Post.%20Collins%20said%20she%20recused%20herself%20from%20the%202018%20deliberations%20for%20the%20national%20reporting%20prize%20because%20the%20Times%20was%20in%20contention%2C%20and%20had%20been%20recused%20from%20the%20subsequent%20discussions%20about%20independent%20investigations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20get%20up%2C%20you%20sit%20in%20the%20hallway%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%2C%20but%20that's%20what%20I%20did%20basically%2C%26quot%3B%20Collins%20recalled%20in%20her%20deposition%2C%20recounting%20the%202018%20board%20meeting%20where%20they%20deliberated%20the%20awards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20some%20point%2C%20somebody%20opens%20the%20door%20and%20says%20come%20on%20back%20in%2C%20we've%20awarded%20the%20prize%20to%20'X%2C'%20and%20then%20you%20come%20back%20and%20the%20next%20series%20comes%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20later%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETrump's%20other%20lawsuits%20over%20'Russiagate'%20have%20failed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20filed%20an%20updated%20version%20of%20the%20suit%20in%20December%202023%2C%20further%20arguing%20he%20was%20subsequently%20vindicated%20by%20Justice%20Department%20Special%20Counsel%20John%20Durham%2C%20who%20investigated%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdurham-special-counsel-report-fbi-investigation-trump-russia-links-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroots%20of%20the%20FBI's%20investigations%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%202016%20Trump%20campaign's%20links%20to%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20members%20asked%20the%20judge%20to%20dismiss%20the%20case%2C%20noting%20that%20a%20different%20judge%20dismissed%20a%20separate%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-federal-judge-throws-russia-trump-lawsuit-fbi-hillary-clinton-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20collusion%20hoax%26quot%3B%20suit%20Trump%20filed%20against%20Hillary%20Clinton%20and%20James%20Comey%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20issued%20nearly%20%241%20million%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-lawyers-sanctioned-by-courts-election-lawsuits-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esanctions%20against%20the%20former%20president's%20lawyers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20that%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20petty%20effort%20by%20one%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20men%20in%20the%20world%20to%20silence%20speech%20he%20dislikes%2C%20filed%20in%20a%20county%20where%20neither%20he%20nor%20any%20of%20the%20defendants%20lives%20or%20works%20or%20has%20any%20meaningful%20connections%20whatsoever%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyers%20filed%20a%20separate%20motion%20for%20Brown%2C%20arguing%20the%20judge%20should%20dismiss%20the%20suit%20because%20the%20awards%20were%20simply%20not%20defamatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBird%20didn't%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment.%20Chad%20Bowman%2C%20a%20Ballard%20Spahr%20attorney%20representing%20the%20Pulitzer%20board%20members%2C%20directed%20Business%20Insider%20to%20court%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22donald%20trump%20at%20mar%20a%20lago%20florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ea20aace7f1785b2e79128%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERepublican%20presidential%20candidate%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20arrives%20at%20a%20Super%20Tuesday%20election%20night%20party%20at%20Mar-a-Lago%20in%20Palm%20Beach%2C%20Florida.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FEvan%20Vucci%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20also%20previously%20filed%20separate%20lawsuits%20against%20the%20Times%20and%20Post%20in%20the%20United%20States%20over%20opinion