3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pick-choose-health-insurance-plan-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealth%20insurance%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20know%20what's%20covered%20and%20how%20much%20you're%20responsible%20for%20paying.%20Try%20to%20match%20your%20policy%20to%20the%20bill%20you%20got%2C%20Gordon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20may%20actually%20need%20to%20be%20the%20one%20who%20crosswalks%20between%20what%20your%20coverage%20is%20and%20what%20they%20billed.%20You%20can't%20assume%20that%20that%20happened%20correctly%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20there%20may%20be%20benefits%20you%20didn't%20know%20were%20covered%20in%20your%20policy.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20gold%20in%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20McIlwain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EUse%20a%20benchmark%20to%20negotiate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFind%20out%20if%20the%20charges%20you%20were%20billed%20were%20reasonable%20compared%20with%20a%20benchmark.%20If%20they%20aren't%2C%20use%20the%20benchmark%20to%20negotiate%20your%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcIlwain%20suggested%20using%20a%20resource%20like%20Healthcare%20Blue%20Book%20to%20look%20up%20average%20fees%20for%20a%20particular%20service%20in%20a%20patient's%20location.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Virgie%20Bright%20Ellington%2C%20author%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrushmedicaldebt.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECrush%20Medical%20Debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20recommended%20using%20an%20AI%20search%20tool%20like%20ChatGPT%20to%20look%20up%20what%20Medicare%20pays%20on%20average%20for%20a%20certain%20service%20based%20on%20the%20service's%20unique%20medical%20code%2C%20called%20a%20CPT%20code.%20(You%20could%20also%20Google%20for%20this%20information%2C%20though%20it%20might%20take%20longer%2C%20she%20said.)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kff.org%2Fmedicare%2Fissue-brief%2Fhow-much-more-than-medicare-do-private-insurers-pay-a-review-of-the-literature%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMedicare%20pays%20lower%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20private%20health%20insurers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20that%20Medicare%20rate%20and%20tell%20the%20hospital's%20billing%20department%20that%20it's%20what%20you're%20willing%20and%20able%20to%20pay%20under%20an%20interest-free%20payment%20plan%20within%20your%20budget%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20profitable%20for%20them%20for%20you%20to%20pay%20something%2C%20and%20they're%20still%20able%20to%20make%20a%20profit%20at%20Medicare%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20Ellington%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPrevent%20a%20bigger%20bill%20by%20questioning%20all%20those%20tests%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20might%20order%20a%20bunch%20of%20costly%20medical%20tests%2C%20but%20you%20may%20not%20need%20them%20all%2C%20McIlwain%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202015%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Facem.12625%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20Academic%20Emergency%20Medicine%20found%20that%2085%25%20of%20doctors%20who%20responded%20said%20they%20believed%20too%20many%20diagnostic%20tests%20were%20ordered%20in%20their%20emergency%20departments.%20Almost%20all%20of%20them%20said%20at%20least%20some%20imaging%20studies%20they%20ordered%20were%20unnecessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20those%20tests%20add%20to%20the%20bill.%20McIlwain%20said%20patients%20can%20avoid%20unnecessary%20tests%20by%20participating%20in%20the%20doctor's%20care%20decisions.%20Ask%3A%20%26quot%3BCan%20we%20discuss%20what%20the%20options%20look%20like%20so%20I%20can%20make%20a%20smart%20decision%20for%20myself%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20tough%20to%20think%20clearly%20when%20you're%20in%20pain%20or%20afraid.%20Gordon%20suggested%20bringing%20a%20friend%20or%20family%20member%20to%20the%20hospital%20who%20can%20be%20level-headed%20and%20ask%20hard%20questions%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20all%20it%20takes%20is%20someone%20asking%20the%20questions%20to%20give%20the%20provider%20pause%20and%20reason%20to%20consider%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%20explain%20it%20and%20make%20sure%20you're%20on%20board%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Gordon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBe%20smart%20about%20where%20and%20when%20to%20get%20care%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20few%20other%20things%20you%20can%20do%20to%20avoid%20a%20big%20medical%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it's%20not%20a%20true%20life-and-death%20emergency%2C%20shop%20around%20for%20care.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Furgent-care-is-changing-how-americans-access-healthcare-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUrgent%20care%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eare%20cheaper%20than%20emergency%20departments.%20For%20planned%20services%2C%20hospitals%20tend%20to%20offer%20price%20estimator%20tools%20you%20can%20use%20to%20get%20an%20idea%20of%20what%20a%20visit%20or%20procedure%20could%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBe%20sure%20to%20visit%20a%20doctor%20in%20your%20health%20insurer's%20network%2C%20as%20going%20out%20of%20network%20can%20lead%20to%20higher%20costs.%20The%20No%20Surprises%20Act%2C%20which%20went%20into%20effect%20in%202022%2C%20protects%20US%20patients%20from%20surprise%20out-of-network%20medical%20bills%20for%20most%20emergency%20services%2C%20and%20when%20patients%20inadvertently%20see%20an%20out-of-provider%20at%20an%20in-network%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcIlwain%20also%20said%20patients%20should%20try%20to%20get%20the%20healthcare%20procedures%20they%20know%20they%20need%20in%20one%20calendar%20year%20to%20maximize%20insurance%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcIlwain%2C%20for%20example%2C%20said%20she%20recently%20was%20cycling%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20ER%20because%20of%20a%20heart%20condition.%20A%20cardiologist%20in%20September%20recommended%20an%20ablation%20%E2%80%94%20treatment%20for%20an%20irregular%20heartbeat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcIlwain%2