20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fschool-17-1709819752.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Samit%20Founder%20of%20Barefoot%20at%20Havelock%20Sawhny.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fschool-17-1709819752.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fschool-17-1709819752-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fschool-17-1709819752-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fschool-17-1709819752-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fschool-17-1709819752-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344272%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESamit%20Sawhny%2C%20Founder%20of%20Barefoot%20at%20Havelock.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamit%20got%20a%20plot%20of%20land%20beside%20the%20beach%20and%20decided%20to%20build%20a%20forest%20around%20it.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20lands%20on%20the%20island%20were%20only%20allocated%20to%20people%20who%20cultivated%20bananas%2C%20rice%2C%20and%20coconut%2C%20or%20to%20parks%2C%20sanctuaries%2C%20and%20reserves%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20Samit%20started%20a%20banana%20plantation%20and%20built%20his%20resort%20in%20a%20way%20that%20merges%20with%20the%20nature%20in%20it.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20resort%20is%20not%20a%20standalone%20in%20essence.%20We%20wanted%20to%20bring%20the%20island%20on%20the%20map%2C%20which%20is%20why%20I%20started%20a%20travel%20company%20to%20help%20plan%20itineraries%20around%20the%20island.%20I%20also%20started%20Barefoot%20Scuba%20which%20is%20a%20scuba%20diving%20centre%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESustainable%2C%20nature-friendly%2C%20and%20a%20hidden%20gem%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConstantly%20listed%20among%20the%20top%20eco-friendly%20resorts%20in%20the%20country%2C%20Samit%20says%20he%20incorporated%20a%20lot%20of%20sustainable%20elements%20during%20the%20construction.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20a%20few%20things%20that%20we%20did%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20we%20used%20natural%20materials%20like%20mud%2C%20wood%2C%20and%20thatch%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20building.%20All%20our%20rooms%20and%20common%20areas%20are%20made%20in%20a%20way%20that%20they%20look%20like%20a%20part%20of%20nature%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20have%20natural%20pathways%20with%20no%20concrete%20on%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%20adding%20that%20the%20resort%20uses%20very%20low%20lighting%20as%20they%20have%20four%20different%20varieties%20of%20owls%20that%20stay%20on%20the%20property.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20moment%20you%20turn%20bright%20lights%20on%2C%20they%20fly%20away.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20disturb%20the%20birds%2C%20so%20we%20give%20flashlights%20to%20the%20guests%20and%20ask%20them%20to%20use%20the%20light%20only%20when%20needed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20resort%20also%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2Fcsr-update%2Fnestle-indias-csr-project-hilldaari-pioneering-sustainable-waste-management-in-tourist-cities%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaste%20management%20system%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20place.%20%E2%80%9CKitchen%20wastewater%20flows%20through%20grease%20traps%2C%20and%20sewage%20is%20directed%20into%20septic%20tanks%20before%20being%20taken%20through%20our%20sewage%20treatment%20plant.%20Wastewater%20flows%20into%20soak%20pits%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20natural%20purification%20process%20then%20takes%20over%2