0military%20training%20and%20arms%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irrawaddy.com%2Fnews%2Fburma%2Faa-offers-save-haven-to-rohingya-targeted-for-conscription-by-myanmar-junta.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%25E2%2580%259CI%2520would%2520like%2520to%2520urge%2Ca%2520press%2520conference%2520on%2520Monday.%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20Irrawaddy.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhine%20told%20reporters%20that%20the%20Junta%E2%80%99s%20military%20%E2%80%9Cno%20longer%20has%20control%20in%20the%20Rakhine%20State%20and%20is%20in%20retreat%2C%20and%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20deliberately%20looking%20to%20instigate%20new%20armed%20conflicts%20and%20communal%20violence%20in%20Rakhine%20State.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20report%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20of%20February%2023%2C%20at%20least%20400%20Rohingya%20men%20had%20already%20been%20forcibly%20recruited%20from%20villages%20and%20IDP%20(internally%20displaced%20people)%20camps%20in%20Sittwe%20and%20Buthidaung%20townships%20(in%20Rakhine%20State)%20to%20fight%20the%20Arakan%20Army.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuoting%20Rohingya%20activists%20and%20residents%2C%20it%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9COn%20February%2027%2C%20Junta%20troops%20abducted%2040%20relatives%20of%20some%20young%20Rohingya%20camp%20residents%20who%20fled%20conscription.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2029%2C%20the%20Junta%E2%80%99s%20military%20abducted%20107%20Rohingya%20men%20aged%2018%20to%2035%20from%20Kyauk%20Talone%20IDP%20camp%20in%20Kyaukphyu%20Township.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fglobal-development%2F2024%2Ffeb%2F28%2Fmyanmar-military-conscription-law-details%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20since%20the%20Junta%20announced%20the%20conscription%20law%20in%20February%2C%20passport%20offices%20and%20embassies%20in%20the%20country%20have%20been%20flooded%20with%20applications%20by%20common%20citizens%20across%20different%20communities%20to%20secure%20a%20visa%20to%20different%20countries%2C%20particularly%20to%20Thailand.%20The%20report%20said%20it%20is%2C%20however%2C%20difficult%20for%20the%20Rohingya%20men%20to%20flee%20the%20country%20legally%20as%20they%20have%20been%20stripped%20of%20their%20citizenship%2C%20and%20officially%2C%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20belong%20to%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fexternal-affairs%2Frohingya-myanmar-timeline%5C%22%3ETimeline%3A%20Being%20Rohingya%20in%20Myanmar%2C%20From%201784%20to%20Now%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENews%20reports%20have%20also%20come%20from%20other%20parts%20of%20Myanmar%20about%20kidnapping%20of%20youth%20for%20forced%20conscription.%20The%20Junta%20has%20denied%20all%20such%20allegations.%20According%20to%20a%20report%2C%20the%20Junta%20has%20been%20announcing%20through%20loudspeakers%20in%20cities%20like%20Mandalay%20that%20nobody%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20join%20the%20Junta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20recently%20activated%20People%E2%80%99s%20Military%20Service%20Law%2C%20brought%20by%20the%20earlier%20military%20regime%20in%202010%2C%20to%20be%20enacted%20next%20month%2C%20men%20aged%2018%20up%20to%2035%2C%20or%20women%20aged%2018%20to%2027%2C%20can%20be%20conscripted%20for%20up%20to%20five%20years%20if%20needed%20by%20the%20Junta%20from%20April%20onwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmyanmar-junta-activates-a-14-year-old-conscription-law-to-try-and-regain-territories%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20though%20the%20junta%20%E2%80%9Crecently%20clarified%20its%20initial%20announcement%2C%20saying%20that%20women%20will%20not%20be%20conscripted%20for%20now.%20This%20claim%20has%20been%20treated%20with%20scepticism%20by%20the%20public%2C%20however%2C%20and%20many%20women%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20flee.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20few%20weeks%2C%20the%20Arakan%20Army%2C%20part%20of%20the%20Brotherhood%20Alliance%2C%20has%20been%20successful%20in%20taking%20control%20of%20several%20towns%20in%20the%20Rakhine%20State.%20As%20per%20latest%20reports%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irrawaddy.com%2Fnews%2Fburma%2Faa-seizes-ponnagyun-stepping-stone-to-capital-of-myanmars-rakhine-state.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520capture%2520of%2520Ponnagyun%2520allows%2Cmilitary%2520analyst%2520told%2520The%2520Irrawaddy.%5C%22%3Ehas%20taken%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Ponnagyun%20town%2C%20located%20just%2033%20kilometres%20from%20the%20capital%2C%20Sittwe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20ceasefire%20with%20the%20Junta%20has%20been%20signed%20by%20the%20Alliance%20forces%20in%20the%20northern%20Shan%20State%20with%20the%20intervention%20of%20China%2C%20no%20such%20agreement%20exists%20between%20the%20military%20and%20the%20three%20EAOs%20fighting%20jointly%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709813739000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07173201%2Fimage-1913.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fflee-to-liberated-areas-myanmars-arakan-army-urges-rohingyas-to-escape-forced-conscription%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Since%20the%20Junta%20announced%20the%20conscription%20law%20in%20February%2C%20passport%20offices%20and%20embassies%20in%20the%20country%20have%20been%20flooded%20with%20applications%20to%20secure%20a%20visa%20to%20different%20nations.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20for%20Rohingya%20men%20to%20flee%20the%20country%20legally%20as%20they%20have%20been%20stripped%20of%20their%20citizenship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fflee-to-liberated-areas-myanmars-arakan-army-urges-rohingyas-to-escape-forced-conscription%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gaza%20government%20says%20Israel%20returned%2047%20exhumed%20bodies%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709813295000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108301740%2Cimgsize-1504114.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fgaza-government-says-israel-returned-47-exhumed-bodies%2Farticleshow%2F108301811.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108301811.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EIsrael%20has%20returned%20dozens%20of%20bodies%20that%20were%20exhumed%20from%20graves%20in%20Gaza%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Hamas-run%20government%20media%20office.%20These%20bodies%20were%20taken%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20for%20examination%20as%20part%20of%20their%20search%20for%20hostages%20from%20Hamas's%20October%207%20attack.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20AFP%20journalists%20have%20witnessed%20the%20reburial%20of%20bodies%20that%20were%20exhumed%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20in%20November%2C%20December%2C%20and%20January%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20Gaza%20officials.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fgaza-government-says-israel-returned-47-exhumed-bodies%2Farticleshow%2F108301811.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fgaza-government-says-israel-returned-47-exhumed-bodies%2Famp_articleshow%2F108301811.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fgaza-government-says-israel-returned-47-exhumed-bodies%2Famp_articleshow%2F108301811.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20HC%20Orders%20Judicial%20Inquiry%20Into%20Young%20Farmer's%20Death%20at%20Khanauri%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F29190804%2FSKS-funeral.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20high%20court%20on%20Thursday%20(March%207)%20ordered%20a%20judicial%20probe%20to%20investigate%20the%20death%20of%2022-year-old%20farmer%20Shubhkaran%20Singh%20nearly%20two%20weeks%20after%20he%20was%20killed%20at%20Khanauri%20on%20the%20Punjab-Haryana%20border%20in%20the%20ongoing%20Delhi%20Chalo%20agitation%20by%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20interim%20order%2C%20the%20bench%20of%20acting%20Chief%20Justice%20G.S.%20Sandhawalia%20and%20Justice%20Lapita%20Banerji%20said%20that%20the%20court%20is%20of%20the%20considered%20opinion%20that%20the%20investigation%20regarding%20the%20death%20of%20Shubhkaran%20cannot%20be%20entrusted%20solely%20either%20to%20the%20State%20of%20Punjab%20or%20to%20the%20State%20of%20Haryana%20for%20obvious%20reasons%2C%20as%20both%20states%20have%20several%20things%20to%20cover%20up.%3Cb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EIn%20such%20circumstances%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20the%20matter%20needs%20to%20be%20supervised%20by%20a%20committee%20headed%20by%20retired%20judge%20of%20this%20court.%C2%A0%3Cb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CKeeping%20in%20view%20the%20above%2C%20we%E2%80%99ll%20constitute%20a%20committee%20headed%20by%20Justice%20Jaishree%20Thakur%2C%20retired%20judge%20of%20this%20court%2C%20who%20will%20be%20assisted%20by%20Parmod%20Ban%2C%20ADGP%2C%20Punjab%20and%20Amitabh%20Singh%20Dhillon%2C%20ADGP%2C%20Haryana%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20order%20said.%3Cb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20the%20court%20order%2C%20the%20committee%20will%20submit%20a%20report%20on%20which%20police%20authorities%20will%20have%20jurisdiction%20to%20investigate%20the%20death%20of%20Shubhkaran%2C%20as%20the%20place%20of%20occurrence%20and%20the%20cause%20of%20death%20must%20first%20be%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20because%20one%20state%20is%20shirking%20its%20responsibilities%2C%20whereas%20the%20other%20is%20yearning%20to%20take%20control%20of%20the%20investigation%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20court%20also%20added%20that%20the%20cause%20of%20Shubhkaran%E2%80%99s%20death%20and%20identifying%20the%20type%20of%20weapon%20from%20which%20the%20bullet%2Fpellet%20emanated%20would%20also%20fall%20within%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EApart%20from%20that%2C%20the%20high%20court%20bench%20also%20said%20that%20the%20committee%20shall%20also%20examine%20the%20issue%20whether%20the%20force%20which%20was%20used%20(to%20handle%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20agitation)%20was%20commensurate%20with%20the%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20bench%20also%20said%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20compensation%20to%20be%20awarded%20on%20account%20of%20his%20death%20shall%20also%20be%20worked%20on.%20Both%20the%20states%20shall%20provide%20all%20facilities%20to%20the%20retired%20high%20court%20judge%20who%20is%20heading%20the%20committee%20and%20the%20officers%20nominated%20shall%20provide%20full%20assistance%20to%20her.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThis%20exercise%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20within%20a%20month%2C%20said%20the%20bench%2C%20while%20deferring%20the%20matter%20to%20April%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cb%3EProbe%20heading%20nowhere%20so%20far%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20for%20a%20judicial%20probe%20came%20in%20response%20to%20a%20bunch%20of%20public%20interest%20litigations%20alleging%20infringement%20of%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20protest%20peacefully%2C%20as%20well%20as%20seeking%20to%20assign%20responsibility%20for%20Shubhkaran%E2%80%99s%20death%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20action%20on%20the%20part%20of%20both%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20the%20report%20submitted%20by%20Punjab%E2%80%99s%20government%20to%20the%20high%20court%2C%20which%20is%20now%20being%20widely%20shared%20on%20social%20media%2C%20the%20cause%20of%20his%20death%20is%20confirmed%20to%20be%20a%20head%20injury%20caused%20by%20a%20firearm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EShubhkaran%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20Charan%20Singh%2C%20on%20whose%20complaint%20the%20Punjab%20police%20filed%20a%20murder%20case%20last%20week%2C%20alleged%20that%20he%20along%20with%20his%20son%20and%20other%20villagers%20was%20in%20a%20trolley%20at%20Khanauri%20on%20February%2021%20when%20Haryana%20security%20forces%20began%20shelling%20protestors%20farmers%20with%20tear%20gas%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EHe%20further%20said%20that%20when%20they%20went%20into%20nearby%20fields%20afterwards%2C%20the%20shelling%20continued%20towards%20that%20side%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CSoon%2C%20farmer%20leaders%20instructed%20us%20to%20sit%20in%20the%20trolley%20and%20as%20we%20started%20walking%2C%20Shubhkaran%2C%20who%20was%20a%20little%20ahead%20of%20me%2C%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20bullet%20in%20the%20back%20of%20his%20head%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20fell%20and%20was%20taken%20to%20Khanauri%20hospital%2C%20where%20doctors%20declared%20him%20dead%20after%20about%20an%20hour.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EIt%20took%20more%20than%20a%20week%20for%20the%20Punjab%20police%20to%20file%20an%20FIR%20in%20this%20case%2C%20since%20the%20matter%20regarding%20his%20death%20fell%20into%20a%20jurisdiction%20trap%20between%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20after%20the%20Haryana%20police%20claimed%20that%20he%20had%20died%20in%20their%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAfter%20pressure%20from%20farmers%E2%80%99%20union%20leading%20the%20Delhi%20Chalo%20march%2C%20the%20Punjab%20police%20finally%20gave%20in%20and%20filed%20a%20%E2%80%98zero%E2%80%99%20FIR%20into%20his%20death%20on%20the%20night%20of%20February%2029.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EZero%20FIRs%20are%20filed%20in%20case%20of%20jurisdictional%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EBut%20since%20then%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20material%20progress%20in%20the%20probe%20into%20the%20circumstances%20leading%20to%20Shubhkaran%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20even%20as%20the%20Punjab%20government%20paid%20him%20homage%20before%20its%20budget%20session%20and%20even%20announced%20Rs%201%20crore%20financial%20relief%20to%20his%20family%20and%20a%20government%20job%20for%20his%20sister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EOn%20the%20day%20of%20Shubhkaran%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20the%20Haryana%20police%20claimed%20in%20the%20high%20court%20that%20a%20team%20was%20constituted%2C%20headed%20by%20DSP%20Jitendra%20Kumar%20of%20Jind%2C%20which%20attempted%20to%20approach%20Government%20Rajindra%20Hospital%2C%20Patiala%20(where%20Shubhkaran%E2%80%99s%20body%20was%20kept)%2C%20to%20conduct%20the%20postmortem%20and%20record%20statements%20from%20the%20deceased%E2%80%99s%20family%20members.%20However%2C%20they%20were%20not%20allowed%20by%20the%20Punjab%20police%20due%20to%20the%20prevailing%20law%20and%20order%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20Bikram%20Singh%20Majithia%2C%20a%20senior%20leader%20of%20the%20Shiromani%20Akali%20Dal%2C%20hit%20out%20at%20both%20the%20AAP%20government%20in%20Punjab%20and%20the%20BJP%20government%20in%20Haryana%20and%20said%20that%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20post-mortem%20confirmed%20his%20death%20due%20to%20a%20firearm%20injury%2C%20the%20investigation%20into%20his%20death%20has%20seen%20no%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EShubhkaran%E2%80%99s%20family%20initially%20declined%20government%20compensation%20but%20later%20accepted%20it%20after%20the%20Punjab%20police%E2%80%99s%20zero%20FIR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EMeanwhile%2C%20according%20to%20advocate%20Uday%20Pratap%20Singh%2C%20the%20high%20court%20also%20questioned%20the%20Haryana%20government%20on%20what%20kind%20of%20bullets%20and%20pellets%20its%20police%20had%20used%20on%20farmers%20and%20asked%20for%20details%20on%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EEver%20since%20the%20latest%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protest%20began%20on%20February%2013%2C%20farmers%E2%80%99%20unions%20have%20alleged%20that%20the%20Haryana%20police%20used%20pellets%20and%20rubber%20bullets%20to%20disperse%20protesters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20data%20from%20Punjab%E2%80%99s%20health%20officials%2C%20more%20than%20180%20farmers%20have%20sustained%20injuries%20and%20many%20suffered%20laceration%20injuries%20due%20to%20tear%20gas%20shelling%20from%20the%20Haryana%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20Haryana%20police%20too%20claimed%20several%20injuries%20to%20their%20staff%20as%20result%20of%20clashes%20with%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3ESeveral%20farmers%20as%20well%20as%20police%20officials%20have%20died%20over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20protest%20due%20to%20heart%20attacks%20among%20other%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20has%20been%20updated%20with%20the%20court%20order%20details.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709813077000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F29190804%2FSKS-funeral.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpunjab-and-haryana-hc-orders-judicial-inquiry-into-young-farmers-death-at-khanauri%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court's%20order%20of%20a%20judicial%20probe%20into%20Shubhkaran%20Singh's%20death%20nearly%20two%20weeks%20ago%20came%20after%20it%20was%20noted%20that%20both%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20had%20failed%20to%20initiate%20proper%20investigations%20into%20his%20death.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpunjab-and-haryana-hc-orders-judicial-inquiry-into-young-farmers-death-at-khanauri%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'7.4%20Lakh%20People%20Evicted%2C%201.53%20Lakh%20Homes%20Demolished%20by%20Govt%20in%20the%20Last%20Two%20Years'%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F16172609%2FUntitled-design-2021-07-16T172559.085.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Around%207.4%20lakh%20people%20were%20forcefully%20evicted%20from%20their%20homes%20across%20rural%20and%20urban%20India%20by%20state%20authorities%20%E2%80%93%20at%20local%2C%20state%20and%20central%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20in%202022%20and%202023%2C%20a%20new%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20same%20period%2C%20state%20authorities%20demolished%20over%201.53%20lakh%20homes%20across%20the%20country%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%20released%20by%20advocacy%20group%20Housing%20and%20Land%20Rights%20Network%20(HLRN).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20figures%20only%20reflect%20cases%20documented%20by%20HLRN%20through%20primary%20and%20secondary%20data%20collection%20in%2023%20states%20and%20four%20union%20territories%2C%20it%20estimates%20that%20the%20actual%20number%20of%20persons%20evicted%20or%20displaced%20across%20India%20in%20this%20period%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20much%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HLRN%20also%20noted%20that%20in%20%E2%80%9Cnearly%20all%20of%20the%20documented%20cases%20of%20forced%20eviction%2C%20state%20authorities%20did%20not%20follow%20due%20process%E2%80%9D%20established%20by%20national%20and%20international%20human%20rights%20standards%20and%20in%20fact%2C%20resulted%20in%20multiple%20and%20gross%20human%20rights%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDemolition%20drives%2C%20in%20many%20instances%2C%20were%20carried%20out%20with%20a%20level%20of%20severity%20and%20brutality%2C%20surpassing%20that%20of%20previous%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhlrn.org.in%2Fdocuments%2FForced_Evictions_2022_2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Forced%20Evictions%20in%20India%202022%20and%202023%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20states%20that%20there%20has%20been%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20forced%20evictions%20through%20court%20orders%20and%20their%20subsequent%20implementation%20by%20state%20authorities.%20The%20HLRN%20uses%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%98forced%20eviction%E2%80%99%20as%20provided%20by%20the%20General%20Comment%207%20(1997)%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20Committee%20on%20Economic%2C%20Social%20and%20Cultural%20Rights.%20According%20to%20that%2C%20a%20forced%20eviction%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpermanent%20or%20temporary%20removal%20against%20the%20will%20of%20individuals%2C%20families%20or%20communities%20from%20their%20homes%20or%20land%2C%20which%20they%20occupy%2C%20without%20the%20provision%20of%2C%20and%20access%20to%2C%20appropriate%20forms%20of%20legal%20or%20other%20protection.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmuslims-targeted-in-128-demolitions-617-people-affected-amnesty-reports-on-bulldozer-action%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Muslims%20Targeted%20in%20128%20Demolitions%2C%20617%20People%20Affected%E2%80%99%3A%20Amnesty%20Reports%20on%20Bulldozer%20Action%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%20and%202023%2C%20around%203%20lakh%20people%20were%20evicted%20due%20to%20court%20orders%2C%20the%20HLRN%20found.%20In%202022%2C%20court%20orders%20resulted%20in%20the%20eviction%20of%20over%2033%2C360%20persons%20while%20in%202023%20this%20figure%20nearly%20touched%202.6%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20courts%20have%20constructively%20interpreted%20the%20law%20to%20provide%20relief%20in%20cases%20of%20housing%20rights%20violations%2C%20despite%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20statute%2C%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20several%20state%20high%20courts%20consistently%20affirming%20the%20right%20to%20housing%20or%20shelter%20as%20an%20inherent%20component%20of%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20life%2C%20the%20HLRN%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20landmark%20judgments%20in%20%3Cem%3ESudama%20Singh%20v.%20Government%20of%20Delhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2010)%20and%20%3Cem%3EAjay%20Maken%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2019)%20%E2%80%9Cplace%20the%20duty%20on%20state%20authorities%20to%20conduct%20a%20survey%20and%20provide%20rehabilitation%20before%20carrying%20out%20any%20forcible%20act%20of%20eviction.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20the%20HLRN%20report%20notes%2C%20recent%20court%20orders%20related%20to%20evictions%2C%20particularly%20in%20Delhi%2C%20have%20deviated%20from%20these%20precedents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20there%20were%20around%20178%20incidents%20of%20demolitions%20recorded%20in%20the%20country%2C%20across%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%2C%20in%202022%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20demolition%20of%2046%2C371%20houses%20and%20forced%20eviction%20of%202.3%20lakh%20persons.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20figures%20jumped%20exponentially%20as%20the%20HLRN%20documented%20146%20cases%20of%20demolitions%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20demolition%20of%20107%2C%20499%20homes%20and%20the%20forced%20eviction%20of%20at%20least%205.15%20lakh%20persons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20for%202023%20are%20the%20highest%20recorded%20figure%20in%20the%20last%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HLRN%20calculated%20that%20at%20least%20294%20houses%20were%20destroyed%20daily%20and%2058%20people%20evicted%20every%20hour%20in%202023%2C%20while%20in%202022%20at%20least%20129%20houses%20were%20destroyed%20daily%20and%2025%20people%20evicted%20every%20hour.%20From%202017%20to%202023%2C%20over%201.68%20million%20people%20were%20evicted%20from%20their%20homes%20and%20around%2017%20million%20people%20live%20under%20the%20threat%20of%20eviction%20and%20displacement%2C%20the%20HLRN%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20major%20demolition%20drives%20that%20affected%20large%20groups%20of%20people%20included%20the%20ones%20in%20Tughlakabad%20(Delhi)%2C%20Rama%20Pir%20No%20Tekro%20(Ahmedabad)%20and%20Faizabad%E2%80%94Naya%20Ghat%20(Ayodhya).%20Forced%20evictions%20of%20the%20urban%20and%20rural%20poor%20occurred%20in%20megacities%2C%20smaller%20cities%2C%20towns%20and%20villages%2C%20with%20Gurgaon%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Ahmedabad%2C%20Ayodhya%2C%20Surat%20and%20Navi%20Mumbai%20among%20those%20heavily%20affected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-unconstitutionality-of-bulldozer-justice%5C%22%3EThe%20Unconstitutionality%20of%20%E2%80%98Bulldozer%20Justice%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20HLRN%2C%2059%25%20or%20the%20maximum%20number%20of%20people%20evicted%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years%20were%20evicted%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20%E2%80%98slum%20or%20land%20clearance%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98encroachment%20removal%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98city%20beautification%E2%80%99%20drives.%20More%20than%202.9%20lakh%20persons%20were%20evicted%20like%20this%20in%202023%20and%20over%201.43%20lakh%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CForced%20evictions%20were%20also%20carried%20out%20for%20a%20range%20of%20other%20reasons%2C%20including%20infrastructure%20and%20ostensible%20%E2%80%98development%E2%80%99%20projects%2C%20including%20%E2%80%98smart%20city%E2%80%99%20projects%3B%20environmental%20projects%2C%20forest%20protection%2C%20and%20wildlife%20conservation%3B%20%E2%80%98disaster%20management%E2%80%99%20efforts%2C%20among%20other%20reasons%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20HLRN%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20most%20cases%20of%20forced%20evictions%2C%20the%20affected%20persons%20and%20communities%20are%20not%20provided%20with%20the%20reason%20for%20their%20eviction%20or%20demolition%20of%20their%20homes.%20However%2C%20based%20on%20available%20data%2C%20the%20report%20identifies%20five%20broad%20categories%20under%20which%20forced%20evictions%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20slum%20clearance%2C%20infrastructure%20and%20ostensible%20development%20projects%2C%20including%20road%20widening%2C%20highway%20expansion%2C%20bridge%20construction%20and%20%E2%80%98smart%20city%E2%80%99%20projects%20contributed%20to%2035%25%20of%20the%20affected%20persons.%20Another%204.7%25%20were%20attributed%20to%20environmental%20projects%2C%20forest%20protection%20and%20wildlife%20conservation.%20The%20remaining%20were%20attributed%20to%20disaster%20management%20efforts%2C%20tourism%20projects%2C%20and%20government-constructed%20low-income%20housing%20units%20being%20declared%20as%20%E2%80%98unsafe%E2%80%99%20for%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20notes%20that%20several%20incidents%20of%20evictions%20were%20%E2%80%9Cseemingly%20carried%20out%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98punitive%20measure%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20for%20instance%20Khargone%20(Madhya%20Pradesh)%2C%20Prayagraj%20and%20Saharanpur%20(Uttar%20Pradesh)%2C%20Nuh%20(Haryana)%20and%20Jahangirpuri%20(Delhi).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20the%20National%20Capital%20Territory%20of%20Delhi%20recorded%20the%20most%20incidents%20of%20evictions%2C%20with%20around%202.8%20lakh%20persons%20evicted%20there%20in%202023%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20resettlement%20of%20the%20displaced%20and%20evicted%20remains%20a%20major%20concern.%20According%20to%20the%20HLRN%2C%20out%20of%20the%20total%20324%20instances%20of%20forced%20evictions%20recorded%20in%202023%20and%202022%2C%20information%20on%20resettlement%20was%20available%20only%20for%20122%20cases.%20Among%20these%2C%20the%20state%20offered%20some%20form%20of%20resettlement%20or%20alternative%20housing%20in%20only%2025%20of%20the%20affected%20sites%20(20.5%25%20of%20total%20instances)%3B%20partial%20resettlement%20in%20seven%20sites%20(1.6%20%25)%20and%20monetary%20compensation%20in%20only%20seven%20sites%20(5.7%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20implies%20that%2C%20in%2072%25%20of%20instances%2C%20where%20information%20is%20available%2C%20the%20state%20failed%20to%20resettle%20or%20rehabilitate%20affected%20persons%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20HLRN%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709812801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F07%2F16172609%2FUntitled-design-2021-07-16T172559.085.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2F7-4-lakh-people-evicted-1-53-lakh-homes-demolished-by-govt-in-the-last-two-years-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20%E2%80%98Forced%20Evictions%20in%20India%202022%20and%202023%E2%80%99%20states%20that%20there%20has%20been%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20number%20of%20forced%20evictions%20through%20court%20orders%20and%20their%20subsequent%20implementation%20by%20state%20authorities.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2F7-4-lakh-people-evicted-1-53-lakh-homes-demolished-by-govt-in-the-last-two-years-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hong%20Kong%20court%20affirms%20landmark%20sedition%20conviction%20for%20pro-democracy%20activist%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709811551000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108300724%2Cimgsize-22660.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com