%20were%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaldev%20Singh%20was%20the%20sole%20witness%20among%20the%20four%20families%20who%20saw%20the%20deceased%20bodies%20at%20the%20Civil%20Hospital%2C%20Nakodar%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20February%205%2C%201986.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20autopsies%20of%20all%20four%20were%20conducted%20in%20the%20dead%20of%20the%20night%20and%20they%20were%20unceremoniously%20cremated%20by%20the%20Punjab%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20Baldev%20Singh%20and%20his%20wife%20Baldip%20Kaur%20visit%20their%20ancestral%20village%20of%20Littran%20in%20Jalandhar%E2%80%99s%20Nakodar%20to%20observe%20the%20anniversary%20of%20Saka%20Nakodar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20they%20observed%20the%2038th%20anniversary%20of%20Saka%20Nakodar%20on%20February%204%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESaka%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Punjabi%20means%20a%20historic%20incident%20or%20tragedy%20involving%20rare%20valour%20or%20sacrifice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F27125938%2F1500x500-1024x341.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F27125938%2F1500x500-1024x341.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F27125938%2F1500x500-300x100.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F27125938%2F1500x500.jpeg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-572663%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22280%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFour%20men%20were%20gunned%20down%20in%20Nakodar%20as%20they%20led%20a%20peace%20march%20against%20the%20sacrilege%20of%20Sikhism%E2%80%99s%20holiest%20book.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40sakanakodar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5