2FWCMS_141187%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3E20%20million%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20reflects%20the%20challenges%20in%20accurately%20quantifying%20a%20workforce%20which%20remains%20invisible%20despite%20its%20ubiquitous%20presence%20in%20urban%20centres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDesigning%2C%20delivering%20and%20enforcing%20social%20protection%20for%20domestic%20workers%20is%20challenging%20for%20two%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20written%20contract%2C%20individual%20households%20hesitate%20to%20acknowledge%20their%20role%20and%20responsibility%20as%20%E2%80%98employers%E2%80%99%20as%20private%20homes%20of%20employers%20are%20not%20recognised%20as%20%E2%80%98places%20of%20work%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20implications%20of%20this%20for%20workers%20have%20been%20studied%20widely%2C%20an%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fnewdelhi%2Fwhatwedo%2Feventsandmeetings%2FWCMS_864652%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3EILO-IIHS%20study%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eset%20out%20to%20explore%20employers%E2%80%99%20perspectives%20on%20social%20protection%20and%20their%20willingness%20to%20contribute%20to%20social%20protection%20measures%20for%20domestic%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopendocs.ids.ac.uk%2Fopendocs%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F20.500.12413%2F4071%2FWp232.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%26isAllowed%3Dy%5C%22%3ESocial%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20includes%20insurance%2C%20maternity%20entitlements%20and%20cash%20transfers%20is%20crucial%20for%20those%20in%20informal%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20helps%20these%20workers%2C%20who%20are%20often%20mothers%20themselves%20with%20a%20family%20to%20feed%2C%20cope%20with%20illness%2C%20accidents%2C%20maternity%20leave%20and%20old-age%2C%20unemployment%20or%20disasters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202030%20Agenda%20for%20Sustainable%20Development%2C%20social%20protection%20is%20fundamental%20to%20achieve%20several%20SDG%20goals%3B%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fglobal%2Ftopics%2Fdw4sd%2Fthemes%2Fsp-floor%2FWCMS_558585%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3ESDG1%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0specifically%20calls%20on%20all%20countries%20to%20provide%20social%20security%20to%20all%20to%20end%20poverty%20in%20all%20its%20forms%20everywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20exposed%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2022%2F5%2Freview-urban-affairs%2Frecovery-resilience.html%3F0%3Dip_login_no_cache%253D2fa9f95c8538a4c80a1d621d68e84546%5C%22%3Egaps%20in%20social%20protection%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20domestic%20workers%20being%20among%20the%20worst-hit%20without%20any%20form%20of%20workplace%20benefits%20like%20health%20insurance%20or%20medical%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fnewdelhi%2Fwhatwedo%2Feventsandmeetings%2FWCMS_864652%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3EILO-IIHS%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0conducted%20a%20two-phased%20study%20in%20Bangalore%20and%20Chennai.%20In%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fnewdelhi%2Fwhatwedo%2Fpublications%2FWCMS_864848%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3Efirst%20phase%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20focused%20on%20questions%20of%20recruitment%2C%20income%20security%2C%20and%20employment%20and%20social%20security.%20We%20surveyed%203%2C067%20employer%20households%20that%20engaged%20paid%20domestic%20workers%20in%20Bengaluru%20(1876%20households)%20and%20Chennai%20(1191%20households).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20came%20to%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20the%20employers%20when%20a%20domestic%20worker%20falls%20ill%20or%20is%20pregnant%2C%20the%20dominant%20response%20in%20Bengaluru%20(40%20percent)%20and%20Chennai%20(37%20percent)%20was%20that%20employers%20should%20support%20expenses%20of%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2028%20percent%20of%20households%20across%20both%20cities%20that%20noted%20that%20employers%20should%20give%20sick%20leave%2C%20about%2059%20percent%20and%2044%20percent%20in%20Bangalore%20and%20Chennai%20respectively%20noted%20that%20employers%20must%20provide%20paid%20sick%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20found%20considerable%20variation%20on%20whether%20employers%20should%20support%20expenses%20of%20treatment%20in%20full%20or%20in%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20maternity%20entitlements%2C%20only%2036%20percent%20of%20households%20in%20Bangalore%20and%2016%20percent%20in%20Chennai%20reported%20support%20for%20maternity%20leave%20with%20either%20full%20or%20partial%20salary%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmployers%20supported%20letting%20a%20worker%20go%20with%20a%20lump%20sum%20payment%20if%20they%20got%20pregnant%20(31%20percent%20in%20Bangalore%20and%2043%20percent%20in%20Chennai)%2C%20leave%20without%20salary%20(20%20percent%20in%20Bangalore%20and%2024%20percent%20in%20Chennai)%20and%20the%20sack%20without%20offering%20any%20money%20(9%20percent%20in%20Bangalore%20and%2012%20percent%20in%20Chennai).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ilo.org%2Fnewdelhi%2Fwhatwedo%2Fpublications%2FWCMS_864849%2Flang--en%2Findex.htm%5C%22%3Esecond%20phase%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20study%2C%20using%20the%20same%20sampling%20strategy%20as%20the%20first%20phase%2C%20we%20conducted%20qualitative%20interviews%20with%20a%20separate%20set%20of%20403%20households%20from%2016%20different%20neighbourhoods%20across%20Bengaluru%20and%20Chennai%20to%20understand%20existing%20practices%20in%20providing%20social%20protection%20for%20domestic%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20employers%20reported%20already%20supporting%20their%20workers%20with%20financial%20aid%20and%20credit%20for%20children%E2%80%99s%20education%2C%20covering%20the%20cost%20of%20treatment%20during%20illness%20and%20other%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20while%20employers%20supported%20the%20idea%20of%20maternity%20leave%2C%20they%20did%20not%20necessarily%20implement%20it.%20Instead%2C%20they%20reflected%20on%20the%20challenges%20it%20posed%20in%20making%20arrangements%20with%20their%20workers.%20They%20asked%20their%20workers%20to%20find%20a%20replacement%20and%20could%20not%20afford%20regular%20payment%20to%20the%20former%20worker%20if%20she%20availed%20maternity%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20they%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20contribute%20to%20a%20formal%20social%20protection%20programme%2C%20we%20found%20three%20broad%20sets%20of%20responses%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEmployers%20that%20were%20willing%20to%20contribute%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20open%20to%20contributing%20to%20workers%E2%80%99%20medical%20insurance%20or%20obtaining%20group%20insurance%20(with%20multiple%20employers)%20for%20their%20employees.%20Some%20employers%20preferred%20to%20deduct%20a%20percentage%20from%20workers%E2%80%99%20salaries%20for%20future%20medical%20expenses%20or%20retirement.%20Others%20were%20willing%20to%20pay%20an%20additional%20amount%20ranging%20from%205%20to%2020%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEmployers%20that%20were%20hesitant%20to%20contribute%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20expressed%20lack%20of%20knowledge%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20take%20up%20procedural%20responsibility%20anticipating%20complicated%20documentation%20and%20paperwork.%20Many%20were%20also%20sceptical%20about%20the%20effectiveness%20and%20sustainability%20of%20formal%20social%20protection%20schemes%2C%20fearing%20that%20the%20system%20might%20lack%20accountability%20or%20eventually%20die%20out.%20Some%20suggested%20that%20instead%20of%20setting%20up%20provident%20funds%20and%20insurance%20mechanisms%2C%20safeguarding%20workers%E2%80%99%20actual%20salaries%20might%20be%20more%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EEmployers%20that%20were%20unwilling%20to%20contribute%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20considered%20the%20additional%20cost%20of%20social%20protection%20as%20being%20a%20financial%20burden%20that%20they%20could%20not%20afford%20as%20they%20were%20already%20responsible%20for%20salaries.%20They%20suggested%20government%20medical%20insurance%20or%20financial%20aid%20to%20domestic%20workers%20to%20ease%20the%20financial%20burden%20on%20both%20employers%20and%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20shows%20that%20a%20vast%20range%20of%20practices%20exist%20in%20employer%20homes.%20While%20several%20employers%20provided%20direct%20financial%20or%20in-kind%20%E2%80%98support%E2%80%99%20to%20their%20workers%20it%20was%20often%20meted%20out%20as%20a%20form%20of%20benevolence%20and%20not%20as%20an%20entitlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20form%20of%20social%20protection%20for%20domestic%20workers%20can%20respond%20to%20the%20following%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F00420980231186077%5C%22%3Ewhat%20type%20of%20social%20protection%20is%20needed%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20data%20shows%20that%20while%20employers%20are%20willing%20to%20provide%20support%20for%20illnesses%20and%20other%20household%20contingencies%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flabour.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fthe_maternity_benefit_act_1961_0.pdf%5C%22%3Ematernity%20entitlements%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0were%20not%20seen%20as%20a%20non-negotiable%20right%20of%20domestic%20workers%20though%20recognised%20by%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocial%20protection%20could%20be%20responsive%20to%20the%20risks%20and%20vulnerabilities%20in%20the%20life%20cycle%20of%20an%20individual%2C%20and%20its%20provisioning%20requires%20tapping%20into%20various%20modes%20of%20delivery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20takes%20us%20to%20who%20is%20responsible%20for%20social%20protection%20for%20domestic%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmployers%20are%20critical%20as%20they%20are%20the%20first%20point%20of%20contact%20for%20workers.%20Addressing%20the%20challenges%20employers%20face%20in%20direct%20provision%20of%20social%20protection%20requires%20a%20coordinated%20effort%20involving%20employers%2C%20workers%20and%20policymakers%20to%20ensure%20that%20domestic%20workers%20receive%20the%20protection%20and%20support%20they%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20possibility%20of%20Resident%20Welfare%20Association-led%20initiatives%20could%20be%20further%20explored%20as%20a%20potential%20avenue%20for%20collectively%20delivering%20social%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20also%20means%20the%20need%20for%20an%20arrangement%20between%20welfare%20boards%20or%20other%20arms%20of%20the%20state%2C%20unions%20and%20workers%2C%20without%20which%20workers%20will%20have%20no%20recourse%20to%20redressal%20in%20case%20employers%20fail%20to%20deliver%20social%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2Fnewsite%2FPrintRelease.aspx%3Frelid%3D187222%5C%22%3ENational%20Policy%20on%20Domestic%20Workers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0outlines%20a%20list%20of%20schemes%20that%20domestic%20workers%20can%20avail%20as%20part%20of%20the%20unorganised%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20schemes%20such%20as%20health%20insurance%2C%20pension%2C%20subsidised%20medical%20facilities%2C%20and%20educational%20support%20for%20children.%20However%2C%20this%20does%20not%20necessarily%20acknowledge%20the%20need%20for%20workplace%20benefits%20that%20are%20linked%20to%20employment%20security%20to%20prevent%20arbitrary%20termination%20from%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20systemic%20neglect%20of%20this%20workforce%20is%20apparent%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20only%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressreleaseshare.aspx%3FPRID%3D1564261%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520State%2520Governments%2520of%2520Andhra%2Cof%2520grievance%2520in%2520this%2520regard.%5C%22%3Efew%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%20included%20domestic%20workers%20in%20the%20schedule%20of%20the%20Minimum%20Wages%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20sector%20wages%20remain%20abysmally%20low%20and%20strongly%20controlled%20by%20employer%20networks%20at%20the%20neighbourhood%20level%20as%20well%20as%20determined%20by%20the%20axis%20of%20workers%E2%80%99%20gender%20(a%20feminised%20workforce%20undertaking%20gendered%20duties)%20and%20caste%20(low%20status%20work%20being%20fulfilled%20by%20marginalised%20communities).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20such%20circumstances%2C%20whether%20from%20employers%2C%20the%20government%20or%20a%20combination%20of%20both%2C%20social%20protection%20is%20an%20absolute%20must%20for%20improving%20labour%20market%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20project%20was%20funded%20by%20the%20International%20Labour%20Organization%20(ILO).%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EDivya%20Ravindranath%20is%20a%20senior%20researcher%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20for%20Human%20Settlements%2C%20Bengaluru.%20Her%20research%20interests%20include%20gender%2C%20informal%20work%2C%20social%20protection%20and%20urban%20health.%20Her%20current%20research%20project%20explores%20care%20infrastructure%20models%20for%20women%20in%20informal%20work.%20She%20holds%20a%20Masters%20and%20PhD%20degree%20in%20Social%20Work%20from%20Tata%20Institute%20for%20Social%20Sciences%20and%20Washington%20University%20in%20St%20Louis%20respectively.%20She%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20Antara%20Rai%20Chowdhury%2C%20Rashee%20Mehra%20and%20Dr.%20Gautam%20Bhan%2C%20her%20co-authors%20on%20the%20ILO-%20IIHS%20report.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0by%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709802011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07133654%2Fdw.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fdomestic-workers-deserve-workplace-benefits%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Employers%20provide%20direct%20financial%20or%20in-kind%20%E2%80%98support%E2%80%99%20to%20their%20workers.%20In%20most%20households%20this%20is%20a%20form%20of%20benevolence%2C%20not%20an%20entitlement.%20This%20can%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fdomestic-workers-deserve-workplace-benefits%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Electoral%20Bond%20Details%20Readily%20Available%3B%20SBI%20Has%20Made%20Up%20Excuse%20For%20Not%20Complying%3A%20Former%20Finance%20Secretary%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07141753%2Fkt-7-march-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20finance%20secretary%20Subhash%20Chandra%20Garg%2C%20who%20was%20economic%20affairs%20secretary%20when%20electoral%20bonds%20were%20first%20introduced%2C%20says%20that%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20needs%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20more%20than%20a%20day%E2%80%9D%20to%20make%20available%20the%20electoral%20bond%20information%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20asked%20the%20bank%20to%20give%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20Garg%20says%20%E2%80%9Cthis%20information%20is%20readily%20available%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9Cit%20is%20available%20at%20the%20click%20of%20a%20button%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20to%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Garg%20says%20that%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20either%20deliberately%20misconstrued%20or%20failed%20to%20understand%20the%20simple%20nature%20of%20the%20six%20bits%20of%20information%20that%20they%20are%20required%20to%20give%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20and%2C%20instead%2C%20the%20bank%20claims%20that%20it%20has%20been%20asked%20to%20collate%20different%20bits%20of%20information%20which%20it%20was%20not%20asked%20to%20do.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20bank%20has%20made%20the%20simple%20things%20required%20of%20it%20seem%20more%20complicated%20and%20long%20drawn%20out%20than%20is%20the%20case.%20This%20has%20given%20the%20SBI%20the%20basis%20on%20which%20to%20argue%20that%20it%20needs%20three%20and%20a%20half%20months%20more%2C%20pushing%20the%20deadline%20to%20June%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGarg%20explained%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20simply%20asked%20for%20six%20simple%20bits%20of%20information%3A%20who%20purchased%20the%20bonds%2C%20the%20date%20and%20the%20amount%20and%20also%20which%20party%20received%20the%20bonds%2C%20when%20they%20were%20encashed%20and%20the%20amount.%20This%20information%20is%20readily%20available.%20The%20electoral%20bond%20guidelines%20of%202018%20themselves%20require%20that%20it%20should%20be%20given%20to%20any%20court%20when%20demanded%20and%20Justice%20Deepak%20Gupta%20has%20revealed%20that%20he%20was%20part%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20which%20in%202019%20ordered%20the%20bank%20to%20maintain%20such%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGarg%20also%20said%20he%20believes%20that%20in%202019%20details%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20sold%20up%20to%20that%20date%20were%20given%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20sealed%20envelope.%20At%20the%20time%20the%20bank%20did%20not%20need%20or%20ask%20for%20extra%20time.%20Why%20do%20they%20need%20extra%20time%20to%20give%20similar%20details%20for%20the%20period%20post%202019%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGarg%20believes%20that%20by%20failing%20to%20meet%20the%20March%206%20deadline%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20is%20already%20guilty%20of%20contempt%20of%20court.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20has%20today%20filed%20a%20contempt%20case%20against%20the%20SBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHas%20this%20become%20a%20test%20case%20for%20the%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20image%20and%20integrity%3F%20How%20embarrassed%20will%20the%20management%20of%20the%20SBI%20be%20today%3F%20What%20would%20be%20the%20impact%20if%20the%20bank%20is%20found%20guilty%20of%20contempt%3F%20Those%20are%20some%20of%20the%20other%20issues%20touched%20upon%20in%20this%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F18gP0yOtuOA%3Fsi%3DZlTqcCjLvpvjWZvh%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709801353000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F07141753%2Fkt-7-march-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwatch-electoral-bond-details-readily-available-sbi-needs-just-a-day-has-made-up-excuse-for-not-complying%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Former%20finance%20secretary%20Subhash%20Chandra%20Garg%20says%20that%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20either%20deliberately%20misconstrued%20or%20failed%20to%20understand%20the%20simple%20nature%20of%20the%20six%20bits%20of%20information%20that%20they%20are%20required%20to%20give%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwatch-electoral-bond-details-readily-available-sbi-needs-just-a-day-has-made-up-excuse-for-not-complying%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Don%E2%80%99t%20cut%20our%20throats%E2%80%99%3A%20Sena%20leader%20warns%20BJP%20over%20LS%20seats%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709796620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108291022%2Cimgsize-12628.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fmumbai%2Fdont-cut-our-throats-and-betray-us-shiv-sena-leader-ramdas-kadam-tells-bjp%2Farticleshow%2F108291062.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22CHAITANYA%20MARP